   NAME
	POPCD - Returns the directory last recently saved with the
	        PUSHCD command.

   FORMAT
	POPCD

   TEMPLATE
	(none)

   PATH
	Internal

   FUNCTION
	POPCD is the counterpart to the PUSHCD command. It will recall the
	directly least recently saved by PUSHCD and return to it. If no
	directory can be popped from the stack, POPCD will return to the
	SYS: directory instead.

   SEE ALSO
	CD, PUSHCD
